Text.SourceString: Even if it's difficult, I believe you can overcome the dark slime.//Do your best, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Even if it's difficult, I believe you can overcome the dark slime.//Do your best, okay?

Text.SourceString: I wish things would go back to the way they were.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish things would go back to the way they were.

Text.SourceString: On one of my patrols with <NPCName>Agung</>, some of the dark slime caught my tail.//It burned for a while after that. Bah!
Text.LocalizedString: On one of my patrols with <NPCName>Agung</>, some of the dark slime caught my tail.//It burned for a while after that. Bah!

Text.SourceString: As a gatekeeper, I took an oath to protect our Kingdom.//<portrait=happy>And in giving you a chance, I feel like I'm honoring that commitment.
Text.LocalizedString: As a gatekeeper, I took an oath to protect our Kingdom.//<portrait=happy>And in giving you a chance, I feel like I'm honoring that commitment.

Text.SourceString: Your arrangement with us is unusual, but, uh, sometimes, unusual situations require unusual solutions, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Your arrangement with us is unusual, but, uh, sometimes, unusual situations require unusual solutions, right?

Text.SourceString: So, you're getting the hang of the barracks, I hope?//Hopefully, the guards aren't causing too much trouble for you.
Text.LocalizedString: So, you're getting the hang of the barracks, I hope?//Hopefully, the guards aren't causing too much trouble for you.

Text.SourceString: Convincing <NPCName>Semeru</> and then escorting you into the Royal palace...it really took a toll on me.
Text.LocalizedString: Convincing <NPCName>Semeru</> and then escorting you into the Royal palace...it really took a toll on me.

Text.SourceString: My parents keep bombarding me with questions about you, the land-dweller.//<portrait=angry>And trust me, I keep telling them the same thing: "Dad, I can't say squat!"//It's like talking to a brick wall.
Text.LocalizedString: My parents keep bombarding me with questions about you, the land-dweller.//<portrait=angry>And trust me, I keep telling them the same thing: "Dad, I can't say squat!"//It's like talking to a brick wall.

Text.SourceString: I hope <NPCName>Semeru</> didn't intimidate you too much.//He may come off as gruff, but deep down, he has a good heart.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope <NPCName>Semeru</> didn't intimidate you too much.//He may come off as gruff, but deep down, he has a good heart.

Text.SourceString: Deeeeep down! Ha ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: Deeeeep down! Ha ha ha!

Text.SourceString: So, you don't have any scales, right? That's, uh, interesting.//<portrait=annoyed>I mean, not having scales, is it... nice?//I, um, really like my scales.
Text.LocalizedString: So, you don't have any scales, right? That's, uh, interesting.//<portrait=annoyed>I mean, not having scales, is it... nice?//I, um, really like my scales.

Text.SourceString: It must've been really challenging for you to reach our kingdom.//<portrait=happy>I can only imagine you're, like, an amazing swimmer, especially for your kind.
Text.LocalizedString: It must've been really challenging for you to reach our kingdom.//<portrait=happy>I can only imagine you're, like, an amazing swimmer, especially for your kind.

Text.SourceString: You might think I'm curious about you, just like you are about me.//<portrait=happy>It's, um, kind of similar in a way, don't you think?
Text.LocalizedString: You might think I'm curious about you, just like you are about me.//<portrait=happy>It's, um, kind of similar in a way, don't you think?

Text.SourceString: I like some land-dwellers, yeah... Like, I've seen pictures of land-dwellers helping injured animals and stuff.//<portrait=blushing>It's kind of them.
Text.LocalizedString: I like some land-dwellers, yeah... Like, I've seen pictures of land-dwellers helping injured animals and stuff.//<portrait=blushing>It's kind of them.

Text.SourceString: I saw the roots retreat away from Empat Pulu... You made that happen, didn't you? You're amazing!
Text.LocalizedString: I saw the roots retreat away from Empat Pulu... You made that happen, didn't you? You're amazing!

Text.SourceString: A part of me feels relieved to see the progress you've made.//If things had gone the other way around, I would've been bombarded with an earful by now.
Text.LocalizedString: A part of me feels relieved to see the progress you've made.//If things had gone the other way around, I would've been bombarded with an earful by now.

Text.SourceString: Might've lost my job too, he he!
Text.LocalizedString: Might've lost my job too, he he!

Text.SourceString: My parents couldn't stop chattering about how great they felt when they woke up this morning. I made sure to pass along their gratitude to you.//So, thank you, <PlayerName>$Player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: My parents couldn't stop chattering about how great they felt when they woke up this morning. I made sure to pass along their gratitude to you.//So, thank you, <PlayerName>$Player</>!

Text.SourceString: I'm rooting for you, <PlayerName>$Player</>! Keep up the good work.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm rooting for you, <PlayerName>$Player</>! Keep up the good work.

Text.SourceString: I appreciate your company, but today I'm just not in the mood for talking.//Sorry about that!
Text.LocalizedString: I appreciate your company, but today I'm just not in the mood for talking.//Sorry about that!

Text.SourceString: Mind if we have a little break from chatting?//Time to tackle some other tasks. Take care!
Text.LocalizedString: Mind if we have a little break from chatting?//Time to tackle some other tasks. Take care!

Text.SourceString: Oops, sorry! Duty calls, and I have to dash. Catch you later!
Text.LocalizedString: Oops, sorry! Duty calls, and I have to dash. Catch you later!

Text.SourceString: We are here to protect the ocean, ensuring that it retains its ability to house all sea creatures. Be sure to help how you can.
Text.LocalizedString: We are here to protect the ocean, ensuring that it retains its ability to house all sea creatures. Be sure to help how you can.

Text.SourceString: Treasures? Are you here for those old chests?//<portrait=normal>There is much more than that down here. Something living and growing... Much much more valuable than silvers.
Text.LocalizedString: Treasures? Are you here for those old chests?//<portrait=normal>There is much more than that down here. Something living and growing... Much much more valuable than silvers.

Text.SourceString: How unfortunate. There is so much to show down here. Too bad all this trash blocks the way forward.
Text.LocalizedString: How unfortunate. There is so much to show down here. Too bad all this trash blocks the way forward.

Text.SourceString: Did I startle you? Forgive me... It's not every day that I see humans cleared out trash down here.//<portrait=annoyed>You look different than the last human that I saw. You seem more <Italic>stretched out</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Did I startle you? Forgive me... It's not every day that I see humans cleared out trash down here.//<portrait=annoyed>You look different than the last human that I saw. You seem more <Italic>stretched out</>.

Text.SourceString: I like some land-dwellers, yeah... Like, I've seen pictures of land-dwellers helping injured animals and stuff.//<portrait=blushing>It's kind of them.
Text.LocalizedString: I like some land-dwellers, yeah... Like, I've seen pictures of land-dwellers helping injured animals and stuff.//<portrait=blushing>It's kind of them.

Text.SourceString: I appreciate your company, but today I'm just not in the mood for talking.//Sorry about that!
Text.LocalizedString: I appreciate your company, but today I'm just not in the mood for talking.//Sorry about that!

Text.SourceString: Mind if we have a little break from chatting?//Time to tackle some other tasks. Take care!
Text.LocalizedString: Mind if we have a little break from chatting?//Time to tackle some other tasks. Take care!

Text.SourceString: Oops, sorry! Duty calls, and I have to dash. Catch you later!
Text.LocalizedString: Oops, sorry! Duty calls, and I have to dash. Catch you later!

Text.SourceString: The octopus that time really had a thing for my hair! Guard duty at the gate is never dull, I tell you.
Text.LocalizedString: The octopus that time really had a thing for my hair! Guard duty at the gate is never dull, I tell you.

Text.SourceString: Manta rays can be so misleading! It gave me quite the scare a couple of times!//<portrait=surprised>Remember when we got a good scare from that manta ray's shadow.
Text.LocalizedString: Manta rays can be so misleading! It gave me quite the scare a couple of times!//<portrait=surprised>Remember when we got a good scare from that manta ray's shadow.

Text.SourceString: Cleaning up can lead to discoveries – like that stunning seashell I found. It’s one of my favorite finds.//<portrait=happy>I still have it tucked away somewhere.
Text.LocalizedString: Cleaning up can lead to discoveries – like that stunning seashell I found. It’s one of my favorite finds.//<portrait=happy>I still have it tucked away somewhere.

Text.SourceString: Confronting that sea creature with my dad almost made my heart jump out of my chest. It’s not every day you get to face challenges like that together.//<portrait=happy>It's kinda cool, don't you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Confronting that sea creature with my dad almost made my heart jump out of my chest. It’s not every day you get to face challenges like that together.//<portrait=happy>It's kinda cool, don't you think?

Text.SourceString: That intense situation with the hostile creature showed me the importance of staying calm and united. Heck yeah! I did it.
Text.LocalizedString: That intense situation with the hostile creature showed me the importance of staying calm and united. Heck yeah! I did it.

Text.SourceString: Trying to make human food for our date was a fun experiment, even if it ended up a bit waterlogged. We still had a great time!
Text.LocalizedString: Trying to make human food for our date was a fun experiment, even if it ended up a bit waterlogged. We still had a great time!

Text.SourceString: I might stick to underwater cooking next time we go on a date.
Text.LocalizedString: I might stick to underwater cooking next time we go on a date.

Text.SourceString: I hope you liked the place I picked for our date. It's one of my favorite spots here.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope you liked the place I picked for our date. It's one of my favorite spots here.

Text.SourceString: I miss you. Where have you been?
Text.LocalizedString: I miss you. Where have you been?

Text.SourceString: Are you here to see me?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you here to see me?

Text.SourceString: We should go on another date sometime.
Text.LocalizedString: We should go on another date sometime.

Text.SourceString: I've been thinking about you. What brings you here today?
Text.LocalizedString: I've been thinking about you. What brings you here today?

Text.SourceString: Hey, <PlayerName>$Player</>, it's nice to see you around.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, <PlayerName>$Player</>, it's nice to see you around.

Text.SourceString: You look really cute in that outfit. The style, um...suits you well.
Text.LocalizedString: You look really cute in that outfit. The style, um...suits you well.

Text.SourceString: That color really brings out your eyes. It's a good look for you.
Text.LocalizedString: That color really brings out your eyes. It's a good look for you.

Text.SourceString: Keep an eye out in the water!//Watch out for those octopuses, they might just surprise you with a new hairdo.
Text.LocalizedString: Keep an eye out in the water!//Watch out for those octopuses, they might just surprise you with a new hairdo.

Text.SourceString: If you see an octopus around, mind your hair! They're curious creatures.
Text.LocalizedString: If you see an octopus around, mind your hair! They're curious creatures.

Text.SourceString: Hold up, just spotted some stray seaweed on that coral over there. Can't leave it looking untidy, give me a second.
Text.LocalizedString: Hold up, just spotted some stray seaweed on that coral over there. Can't leave it looking untidy, give me a second.

Text.SourceString: There's a spot that needs a bit of tidying, and it's been bothering me all day.  I'll take a detour later and clean it up after I'm done here.
Text.LocalizedString: There's a spot that needs a bit of tidying, and it's been bothering me all day.  I'll take a detour later and clean it up after I'm done here.

Text.SourceString: During my next break, I'm thinking of rearranging those rocks over there. They'll look better and improve water flow.
Text.LocalizedString: During my next break, I'm thinking of rearranging those rocks over there. They'll look better and improve water flow.

Text.SourceString: I have a small project later – fixing up the seaweed beds near the East current. They're essential for our marine life.//<portrait=surprised>And it's gonna be so much fun!
Text.LocalizedString: I have a small project later – fixing up the seaweed beds near the East current. They're essential for our marine life.//<portrait=surprised>And it's gonna be so much fun!

Text.SourceString: After our patrol, I have a meeting with a group of crabs. We're going to scout out a new feeding area for them.
Text.LocalizedString: After our patrol, I have a meeting with a group of crabs. We're going to scout out a new feeding area for them.

Text.SourceString: There's an area near the kelp forest I've been monitoring that's due for a cleanup.//I need to make a new bamboo broom since the last one broke. Ugh.
Text.LocalizedString: There's an area near the kelp forest I've been monitoring that's due for a cleanup.//I need to make a new bamboo broom since the last one broke. Ugh.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Agung</>'s hoarding can be a bit much sometimes. I mean, how many shells does one really need?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Agung</>'s hoarding can be a bit much sometimes. I mean, how many shells does one really need?

Text.SourceString: Every time I see <NPCName>Agung</>'s collection, I'm amazed. He just keeps gathering more and more things.
Text.LocalizedString: Every time I see <NPCName>Agung</>'s collection, I'm amazed. He just keeps gathering more and more things.

Text.SourceString: You should see <NPCName>Agung</>'s stash of trinkets and shells. He's got a real knack for hoarding, but I guess everyone needs a hobby.
Text.LocalizedString: You should see <NPCName>Agung</>'s stash of trinkets and shells. He's got a real knack for hoarding, but I guess everyone needs a hobby.

Text.SourceString: Trying to get the crabs organized for the clean-up was like teaching a sea urchin to tango, just not happening.
Text.LocalizedString: Trying to get the crabs organized for the clean-up was like teaching a sea urchin to tango, just not happening.

Text.SourceString: Telling <NPCName>Agung</> to reduce his hoarding is like riding a current with a jellyfish for a saddle – risky and pretty wobbly.
Text.LocalizedString: Telling <NPCName>Agung</> to reduce his hoarding is like riding a current with a jellyfish for a saddle – risky and pretty wobbly.

Text.SourceString: The King is discussing a change in the regulations for kelp noodle imports. As for that new policy change, we'll cross that reef when the tide comes in.//No use worrying about it now.
Text.LocalizedString: The King is discussing a change in the regulations for kelp noodle imports. As for that new policy change, we'll cross that reef when the tide comes in.//No use worrying about it now.

Text.SourceString: The kingdom lost one of the land dwellers' tridents, and <NPCName>Semeru</> suspected that Maharaja Putput might have hidden it.//<portrait=annoyed>So, my job was to keep an eye on Putput while everyone else searched.//Oh, I kept my eyes glued on that little ball, yes, I did.
Text.LocalizedString: The kingdom lost one of the land dwellers' tridents, and <NPCName>Semeru</> suspected that Maharaja Putput might have hidden it.//<portrait=annoyed>So, my job was to keep an eye on Putput while everyone else searched.//Oh, I kept my eyes glued on that little ball, yes, I did.

Text.SourceString: When I eventually located the missing trident, <NPCName>Semeru</>'s happiness was unparalleled - like a dolphin joyfully spinning in a whirlpool.//<portrait=concerned>I'd never seen him so elated before; I hadn't thought him capable of such joy.
Text.LocalizedString: When I eventually located the missing trident, <NPCName>Semeru</>'s happiness was unparalleled - like a dolphin joyfully spinning in a whirlpool.//<portrait=concerned>I'd never seen him so elated before; I hadn't thought him capable of such joy.

Text.SourceString: Getting a laugh out of <NPCName>Semeru</> with our jokes is about as likely as a clam hosting a dance party.//<portrait=angry>You'll never see him crack a smile. <Italic>Neverrr</>!!!
Text.LocalizedString: Getting a laugh out of <NPCName>Semeru</> with our jokes is about as likely as a clam hosting a dance party.//<portrait=angry>You'll never see him crack a smile. <Italic>Neverrr</>!!!

Text.SourceString: You won't believe what I saw on patrol today – a school of fish forming a perfect circle.//<portrait=normal>It was super cool. I wish you had been there to see it.
Text.LocalizedString: You won't believe what I saw on patrol today – a school of fish forming a perfect circle.//<portrait=normal>It was super cool. I wish you had been there to see it.

Text.SourceString: During last week's patrol, I had a close call with a curious squid. It almost grabbed my cleaning brush.
Text.LocalizedString: During last week's patrol, I had a close call with a curious squid. It almost grabbed my cleaning brush.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Agung</> and I once had to chase off some nosy sharks that woke us up at 2 am.//<portrait=happy>Let's just hope they don't come back looking for a job as guards, eh? Haha, that's a <NPCName>Semeru</> joke, get it?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Agung</> and I once had to chase off some nosy sharks that woke us up at 2 am.//<portrait=happy>Let's just hope they don't come back looking for a job as guards, eh? Haha, that's a <NPCName>Semeru</> joke, get it?

Text.SourceString: Ugh. Looks like I've been spending too much time with <NPCName>Agung</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh. Looks like I've been spending too much time with <NPCName>Agung</>.

Text.SourceString: Finally off duty. I'm starving! Time to find something to eat – maybe something other than kelp salad for a change.
Text.LocalizedString: Finally off duty. I'm starving! Time to find something to eat – maybe something other than kelp salad for a change.

Text.SourceString: I feel so tired today. I need to hit the seaweed bed early tonight.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel so tired today. I need to hit the seaweed bed early tonight.

Text.SourceString: Phew, what a day! I think I've earned some relaxation. Maybe I'll just float around and enjoy the quiet for a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: Phew, what a day! I think I've earned some relaxation. Maybe I'll just float around and enjoy the quiet for a bit.

Text.SourceString: I could really go for a snack. Maybe I'll treat myself to some frozen kelp – they're my guilty pleasure.
Text.LocalizedString: I could really go for a snack. Maybe I'll treat myself to some frozen kelp – they're my guilty pleasure.

Text.SourceString: My seaweed bed is starting to fall apart – looks like it's time for a change. I should plant new ones and maybe replace my parents' as well, all in one go.
Text.LocalizedString: My seaweed bed is starting to fall apart – looks like it's time for a change. I should plant new ones and maybe replace my parents' as well, all in one go.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I can get some of those nicely scented seaweeds, but I'll need <NPCName>Olan</> for that. He has a knack for finding the best-smelling seaweed, and since the harvest area is owned by his friends, I'll need him with me to harvest it.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I can get some of those nicely scented seaweeds, but I'll need <NPCName>Olan</> for that. He has a knack for finding the best-smelling seaweed, and since the harvest area is owned by his friends, I'll need him with me to harvest it.

Text.SourceString: This morning, near the eastern gate, I spotted a rare sea turtle – so adorable!//<portrait=concerned>It had some netting around its neck; at first, I thought it was trapped. Thankfully, I didn't snatch it.//<portrait=happy>That could have led to another complaint against me.
Text.LocalizedString: This morning, near the eastern gate, I spotted a rare sea turtle – so adorable!//<portrait=concerned>It had some netting around its neck; at first, I thought it was trapped. Thankfully, I didn't snatch it.//<portrait=happy>That could have led to another complaint against me.

Text.SourceString: While on patrol, I came across a stunning piece of driftwood. It's got the perfect shape for crafting a beautiful bowl.
Text.LocalizedString: While on patrol, I came across a stunning piece of driftwood. It's got the perfect shape for crafting a beautiful bowl.

Text.SourceString: I'm thinking of making it into a birthday gift for my mom.//<portrait=concerned>But now, I have to learn how to make a bowl. Can you help me with that?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm thinking of making it into a birthday gift for my mom.//<portrait=concerned>But now, I have to learn how to make a bowl. Can you help me with that?

Text.SourceString: I can't stand seeing trash on the ocean floor. Thank you for helping us clear it up.
Text.LocalizedString: I can't stand seeing trash on the ocean floor. Thank you for helping us clear it up.

Text.SourceString: Some days I feel like I'm just treading water, not really special at anything.//Do you ever feel like you're just part of the background?
Text.LocalizedString: Some days I feel like I'm just treading water, not really special at anything.//Do you ever feel like you're just part of the background?

Text.SourceString: I often wonder if I'm making a difference or just going with the flow.
Text.LocalizedString: I often wonder if I'm making a difference or just going with the flow.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, my temper flares up and I have to swim away to cool down. It's embarrassing.//ARRRGGGHHHHHH!!!
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, my temper flares up and I have to swim away to cool down. It's embarrassing.//ARRRGGGHHHHHH!!!

Text.SourceString: When things don't go as planned, I can get pretty hot-headed. It's something I'm working on.
Text.LocalizedString: When things don't go as planned, I can get pretty hot-headed. It's something I'm working on.

Text.SourceString: My temper got the better of me today during a disagreement with <NPCName>Agung</>. You could say I got mad at him, yeah...//<portrait=sad>He got scared and tripped over a sleeping turtle. I feel kind of bad about it.
Text.LocalizedString: My temper got the better of me today during a disagreement with <NPCName>Agung</>. You could say I got mad at him, yeah...//<portrait=sad>He got scared and tripped over a sleeping turtle. I feel kind of bad about it.

Text.SourceString: I received a complaint about rearranging what turned out to be an eel village. I honestly didn't realize it was a settlement – it just looked so messy.
Text.LocalizedString: I received a complaint about rearranging what turned out to be an eel village. I honestly didn't realize it was a settlement – it just looked so messy.

Text.SourceString: I understand they might not want it changed, but now their village is neatly organized. It's baffling.//<portrait=annoyed>This whole situation is like trying to hold onto an eel in seaweed oil – it's just so hard to grasp.
Text.LocalizedString: I understand they might not want it changed, but now their village is neatly organized. It's baffling.//<portrait=annoyed>This whole situation is like trying to hold onto an eel in seaweed oil – it's just so hard to grasp.

Text.SourceString: I have a scrapbook of all the interesting things I find on patrol. It's my little hobby.
Text.LocalizedString: I have a scrapbook of all the interesting things I find on patrol. It's my little hobby.

Text.SourceString: I'm thinking of taking up stone painting. There's so much beauty here to capture.//Maybe <NPCName>Rysy</> can teach me how to paint.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm thinking of taking up stone painting. There's so much beauty here to capture.//Maybe <NPCName>Rysy</> can teach me how to paint.

Text.SourceString: I'm adding the most beautiful shell I found today to my scrapbook.//<portrait=normal>But only the drawing, not the shell itself – I don't like bringing things home...they just collect sand.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm adding the most beautiful shell I found today to my scrapbook.//<portrait=normal>But only the drawing, not the shell itself – I don't like bringing things home...they just collect sand.

Text.SourceString: I've been thinking of painting the sunset I saw yesterday on a stone. The only problem is, I'm not quite sure how to do it.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been thinking of painting the sunset I saw yesterday on a stone. The only problem is, I'm not quite sure how to do it.

Text.SourceString: My scrapbook is growing! Oh yeah! Each page is a story of the sea, told through what I find on my patrols.
Text.LocalizedString: My scrapbook is growing! Oh yeah! Each page is a story of the sea, told through what I find on my patrols.

Text.SourceString: Can I sketch the seaweed arrangement if you get married?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I sketch the seaweed arrangement if you get married?

Text.SourceString: Yeah, so?
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, so?

Text.SourceString: Oh, so fun, okay, I require a 50% deposit. How do you want to pay?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, so fun, okay, I require a 50% deposit. How do you want to pay?

Text.SourceString: Oh my clams!!! Are you...I...ah, I'm speechless.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my clams!!! Are you...I...ah, I'm speechless.

Special.SourceString: It's up to you, 'cause it's you I'll be marrying.
Special.LocalizedString: It's up to you, 'cause it's you I'll be marrying.

93.SpecialTag: It's up to you, 'cause it's you I'll be marrying.
93.Question: R3

Text.SourceString: Oh my clams!!! I missed out!//(happy)Oh, well...I wish you a lifetime of happiness, my friend.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh my clams!!! I missed out!//(happy)Oh, well...I wish you a lifetime of happiness, my friend.

Text.SourceString: I wish land-dwellers understood the importance of keeping the ocean clean. It's our home, after all.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish land-dwellers understood the importance of keeping the ocean clean. It's our home, after all.

Text.SourceString: Today, I came across a coral reef that was damaged, looked like it was poisoned by something leaking into the water. I'm scared, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Today, I came across a coral reef that was damaged, looked like it was poisoned by something leaking into the water. I'm scared, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: What if more oil gets down here? That coral...it could've been me or my parents. It's a scary thought.
Text.LocalizedString: What if more oil gets down here? That coral...it could've been me or my parents. It's a scary thought.

Text.SourceString: I'm trying to learn how to make a seaweed blanket. It's harder than it looks.//<portrait=annoyed>My old one tore, and I ended up floating all the way up to the ceiling near the door while I was sleeping.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm trying to learn how to make a seaweed blanket. It's harder than it looks.//<portrait=annoyed>My old one tore, and I ended up floating all the way up to the ceiling near the door while I was sleeping.

Text.SourceString: Let me tell you something. So, I was on duty guarding the queen during her meeting with the dolphins last week.//<portrait=annoyed>Watching the queen handle that dispute with the dolphins was like seeing someone try to calm a storm with a whisper – so complex.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me tell you something. So, I was on duty guarding the queen during her meeting with the dolphins last week.//<portrait=annoyed>Watching the queen handle that dispute with the dolphins was like seeing someone try to calm a storm with a whisper – so complex.

Text.SourceString: It really opened my eyes to how complicated these matters can be.
Text.LocalizedString: It really opened my eyes to how complicated these matters can be.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I wish I could take back my words. Hurting people is the last thing I want.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I wish I could take back my words. Hurting people is the last thing I want.

Text.SourceString: Yeah, maybe I should.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, maybe I should.

Special.SourceString: Perhaps I should consider apologizing? It might help mend things.
Special.LocalizedString: Perhaps I should consider apologizing? It might help mend things.

102.SpecialTag: Perhaps I should consider apologizing? It might help mend things.
102.Question: R1

Text.SourceString: Heated? What do you mean, heated?! Huh?! Explain!//<portrait=sad>Oh, right. Now I get it.
Text.LocalizedString: Heated? What do you mean, heated?! Huh?! Explain!//<portrait=sad>Oh, right. Now I get it.

Special.SourceString: It's true, you can get a bit heated at times.
Special.LocalizedString: It's true, you can get a bit heated at times.

103.SpecialTag: It's true, you can get a bit heated at times.
103.Question: R2

Text.SourceString: Oh, if only that were true. I know I can be a hothead. Recognizing it is one thing, changing it is another.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, if only that were true. I know I can be a hothead. Recognizing it is one thing, changing it is another.

Special.SourceString: You have done nothing wrong. Ever.
Special.LocalizedString: You have done nothing wrong. Ever.

104.SpecialTag: You have done nothing wrong. Ever.
104.Question: R3

Text.SourceString: You see the way that school of fish was behaving? Something's different in the water.
Text.LocalizedString: You see the way that school of fish was behaving? Something's different in the water.

Text.SourceString: I've been observing the tides. They seem to be shifting in a new pattern today.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been observing the tides. They seem to be shifting in a new pattern today.

Text.SourceString: Have you seen the new algae species near the eastern rocks? It's a sign the water's getting warmer.//<portrait=normal>I might not feel the difference, but those little guys sure can. You can trust me on that.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen the new algae species near the eastern rocks? It's a sign the water's getting warmer.//<portrait=normal>I might not feel the difference, but those little guys sure can. You can trust me on that.

Text.SourceString: We should go on a picnic together sometime, just the two of us.//What kind of food do you like, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: We should go on a picnic together sometime, just the two of us.//What kind of food do you like, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: Sushi? What's that? It sounds like the kind of noise a seahorse would make.
Text.LocalizedString: Sushi? What's that? It sounds like the kind of noise a seahorse would make.

Text.SourceString: I've heard of it. Maybe I can try making some seaweed pasta. It could be a fun experiment!
Text.LocalizedString: I've heard of it. Maybe I can try making some seaweed pasta. It could be a fun experiment!

Special.SourceString: I'm a big fan of pasta.
Special.LocalizedString: I'm a big fan of pasta.

110.SpecialTag: I'm a big fan of pasta.
110.Question: R2

Text.SourceString: Simple meals, huh? Got it! I'll have to cook for you sometime then. It's a date!
Text.LocalizedString: Simple meals, huh? Got it! I'll have to cook for you sometime then. It's a date!

Text.SourceString: Oh, <PlayerName>$Player</>. I'm flattered.//<portrait=angry>Wait, you mean me...you're not talking about eating me, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, <PlayerName>$Player</>. I'm flattered.//<portrait=angry>Wait, you mean me...you're not talking about eating me, right?

Text.SourceString: Not much of a talker, huh? That's okay. It's gonna be a surprise then.//I'll have to cook for you sometime. It's a date!
Text.LocalizedString: Not much of a talker, huh? That's okay. It's gonna be a surprise then.//I'll have to cook for you sometime. It's a date!

Text.SourceString: If you ever need tips on navigating the currents, just ask. I know these waters like the back of my hand.
Text.LocalizedString: If you ever need tips on navigating the currents, just ask. I know these waters like the back of my hand.

Text.SourceString: Hey, <PlayerName>$Player</>! It's good to see you around. How's your day going?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, <PlayerName>$Player</>! It's good to see you around. How's your day going?

Text.SourceString: Look who's swimming by! Great to see you here, <PlayerName>$Player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Look who's swimming by! Great to see you here, <PlayerName>$Player</>.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$Player</>! I, uh, was just thinking about you. What a coincidence seeing you here!
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$Player</>! I, uh, was just thinking about you. What a coincidence seeing you here!

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$Player</>! My heart did a little flipper-flip seeing you. Hope your day's going well.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$Player</>! My heart did a little flipper-flip seeing you. Hope your day's going well.

Text.SourceString: Hi, <PlayerName>$Player</>! You always seem to swim into view at the right moment. How are you?
Text.LocalizedString: Hi, <PlayerName>$Player</>! You always seem to swim into view at the right moment. How are you?

Text.SourceString: Back from patrol. Fancy joining me for a quick swim around the reef?
Text.LocalizedString: Back from patrol. Fancy joining me for a quick swim around the reef?

Text.SourceString: I found this interesting shell today. Thought you might like to see it.//<portrait=angry>Oh, dang it! Where was it?!
Text.LocalizedString: I found this interesting shell today. Thought you might like to see it.//<portrait=angry>Oh, dang it! Where was it?!

Text.SourceString: Have you tried nasi laut from the market? They're my go-to dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you tried nasi laut from the market? They're my go-to dinner.

Text.SourceString: There’s this spot near the forest I love. It's peaceful. Maybe I'll show it to you sometime.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s this spot near the forest I love. It's peaceful. Maybe I'll show it to you sometime.

Text.SourceString: Whenever I'm with you, I feel like the luckiest merfolk in the sea.
Text.LocalizedString: Whenever I'm with you, I feel like the luckiest merfolk in the sea.

Text.SourceString: How about we spend the evening just floating and watching the stars? I kinda miss you.
Text.LocalizedString: How about we spend the evening just floating and watching the stars? I kinda miss you.

Text.SourceString: Dad works so hard for the kingdom. Growing up, I've always wanted to be like him.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad works so hard for the kingdom. Growing up, I've always wanted to be like him.

Text.SourceString: Dad used to always bring back weird stuff from his kingdom duties for me. One time, he brought home a coral that glows in the dark.//<portrait=happy>I thought it was the coolest thing in the world.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad used to always bring back weird stuff from his kingdom duties for me. One time, he brought home a coral that glows in the dark.//<portrait=happy>I thought it was the coolest thing in the world.

Text.SourceString: Mom lets me help in the garden sometimes. I try not to mess up, but hey, I'm better at patrolling than planting.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom lets me help in the garden sometimes. I try not to mess up, but hey, I'm better at patrolling than planting.

Text.SourceString: Mom loves to experiment with recipes. Sometimes they're great, sometimes...well, it's the thought that counts!
Text.LocalizedString: Mom loves to experiment with recipes. Sometimes they're great, sometimes...well, it's the thought that counts!

Text.SourceString: This Spring air feels so fresh. It's a nice change.
Text.LocalizedString: This Spring air feels so fresh. It's a nice change.

Text.SourceString: We're off to the Alun-Alun tomorrow for the cherry blossom festival.//You planning to be there?
Text.LocalizedString: We're off to the Alun-Alun tomorrow for the cherry blossom festival.//You planning to be there?

Text.SourceString: The princess is still figuring out what to bring for the potluck.//Good thing we've got a bit more time.
Text.LocalizedString: The princess is still figuring out what to bring for the potluck.//Good thing we've got a bit more time.

Text.SourceString: I really overdid it with the eating yesterday.//<portrait=normal>Never knew soup could be so tasty.
Text.LocalizedString: I really overdid it with the eating yesterday.//<portrait=normal>Never knew soup could be so tasty.

Text.SourceString: Someone brought some fantastic wine to the potluck yesterday. Was that you?//<portrait=normal>I've got to find out where to get it. My parents would really enjoy it, I think.
Text.LocalizedString: Someone brought some fantastic wine to the potluck yesterday. Was that you?//<portrait=normal>I've got to find out where to get it. My parents would really enjoy it, I think.

Text.SourceString: How's it going, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: How's it going, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: Hey there, <PlayerName>$Player</>! How's your day?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey there, <PlayerName>$Player</>! How's your day?

Text.SourceString: Hey, <PlayerName>$Player</>, how's the farm?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, <PlayerName>$Player</>, how's the farm?

Text.SourceString: Baby! It's you! How's it going?
Text.LocalizedString: Baby! It's you! How's it going?

Text.SourceString: How's your day, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: How's your day, babe?

Text.SourceString: Checking up on me, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Checking up on me, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: Good morning! Going somewhere?
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning! Going somewhere?

Text.SourceString: What a beautiful morning!
Text.LocalizedString: What a beautiful morning!

Text.SourceString: Do you feel something weird with your nose too...ugh...it was fine last night.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you feel something weird with your nose too...ugh...it was fine last night.

Text.SourceString: I want to learn to walk in those tall shoes.//<portrait=surprised>Saw someone wearing them at the beach yesterday. Wow, what a skill.
Text.LocalizedString: I want to learn to walk in those tall shoes.//<portrait=surprised>Saw someone wearing them at the beach yesterday. Wow, what a skill.

Text.SourceString: How do you yawn without getting water in your mouth?//It's such a weird feeling. I'm not used to it yet.
Text.LocalizedString: How do you yawn without getting water in your mouth?//It's such a weird feeling. I'm not used to it yet.

Text.SourceString: I like the inn; the rooms are spacious and the beds are super soft.//They must use top-quality kelp or something.
Text.LocalizedString: I like the inn; the rooms are spacious and the beds are super soft.//They must use top-quality kelp or something.

Text.SourceString: I'm a bit nervous about seeing so many land-dwellers tomorrow, but also kind of excited.//Does that make sense?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm a bit nervous about seeing so many land-dwellers tomorrow, but also kind of excited.//Does that make sense?

Text.SourceString: The beach is going to be super crowded tomorrow!
Text.LocalizedString: The beach is going to be super crowded tomorrow!

Text.SourceString: I'm exhausted...think I'm a bit dehydrated from yesterday. I'm planning to take a nap as soon as I get home tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm exhausted...think I'm a bit dehydrated from yesterday. I'm planning to take a nap as soon as I get home tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Semeru</> was going on about possible ghost sightings tomorrow. I don’t really buy it, so I kind of zoned out.//<portrait=normal>But hey, we'll get to see everyone in their fancy outfits!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Semeru</> was going on about possible ghost sightings tomorrow. I don’t really buy it, so I kind of zoned out.//<portrait=normal>But hey, we'll get to see everyone in their fancy outfits!

Text.SourceString: Looking forward to Winter?
Text.LocalizedString: Looking forward to Winter?

Text.SourceString: Excited about the New Year?
Text.LocalizedString: Excited about the New Year?

Text.SourceString: I'm heading to the vineyard tomorrow for New Year's Eve.//Well, more like chaperoning the princess, but I get to join in too.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm heading to the vineyard tomorrow for New Year's Eve.//Well, more like chaperoning the princess, but I get to join in too.

Text.SourceString: Meet me at the vineyard tomorrow, babe. We're going to the New Year's Eve celebration.
Text.LocalizedString: Meet me at the vineyard tomorrow, babe. We're going to the New Year's Eve celebration.

Text.SourceString: If you get bitten by bugs, try not to scratch it! Read it in a book somewhere – you're not supposed to tear your skin.//<portrait=angry>Ugh, it's tough though! So itchy. These land bugs are intense.
Text.LocalizedString: If you get bitten by bugs, try not to scratch it! Read it in a book somewhere – you're not supposed to tear your skin.//<portrait=angry>Ugh, it's tough though! So itchy. These land bugs are intense.

Text.SourceString: I like how my hair feels here on land, all dry... It's kind of rough, but in a good way.//Hard to describe, but it's nice, haha.
Text.LocalizedString: I like how my hair feels here on land, all dry... It's kind of rough, but in a good way.//Hard to describe, but it's nice, haha.

Text.SourceString: It's actually kind of fun being on this duty, haha. Feels a bit like a mini vacation!
Text.LocalizedString: It's actually kind of fun being on this duty, haha. Feels a bit like a mini vacation!

Text.SourceString: My scalp's itchy. I think I'm sweating a lot.
Text.LocalizedString: My scalp's itchy. I think I'm sweating a lot.

Text.SourceString: Oof, every time I go barefoot, my feet start burning!
Text.LocalizedString: Oof, every time I go barefoot, my feet start burning!

Text.SourceString: I've noticed land-dwellers drink a lot of milk.//Every time we order drinks, it's always, 'What kind of milk do you want?' No milk for me, thanks.
Text.LocalizedString: I've noticed land-dwellers drink a lot of milk.//Every time we order drinks, it's always, 'What kind of milk do you want?' No milk for me, thanks.

Text.SourceString: Sweat is weird. It's just the skin evaporating... Nothing to worry about, the healer says.
Text.LocalizedString: Sweat is weird. It's just the skin evaporating... Nothing to worry about, the healer says.

Text.SourceString: Phew! The heat!
Text.LocalizedString: Phew! The heat!

Text.SourceString: A coconut would be really nice right about now.
Text.LocalizedString: A coconut would be really nice right about now.

Text.SourceString: What kind of fruits do you plant in the Fall?
Text.LocalizedString: What kind of fruits do you plant in the Fall?

Text.SourceString: I like your clothes. Where do you pick them up from?
Text.LocalizedString: I like your clothes. Where do you pick them up from?

Text.SourceString: I have to admit, seeing <NPCName>Semeru</> with legs looks a bit funny to me...can't really explain why.//<portrait=annoyed>He looks kind of silly. But then, maybe I look a bit silly too. Hmm...food for thought.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to admit, seeing <NPCName>Semeru</> with legs looks a bit funny to me...can't really explain why.//<portrait=annoyed>He looks kind of silly. But then, maybe I look a bit silly too. Hmm...food for thought.

Text.SourceString: These clothes from the land aren't too different from what we wear.
Text.LocalizedString: These clothes from the land aren't too different from what we wear.

Text.SourceString: It's getting colder, isn't it? Last time we were here, it was so hot!
Text.LocalizedString: It's getting colder, isn't it? Last time we were here, it was so hot!

Text.SourceString: I was chatting with the inn owner, and she mentioned pumpkin coffee and pumpkin pies.//I get the pies, but in coffee? It sounds...well, it sounds interesting.
Text.LocalizedString: I was chatting with the inn owner, and she mentioned pumpkin coffee and pumpkin pies.//I get the pies, but in coffee? It sounds...well, it sounds interesting.

Text.SourceString: Kinda wish <NPCName>Semeru</> would loosen up a bit, so I could chill more.//<portrait=surprised>Oops, hope he didn't hear that.
Text.LocalizedString: Kinda wish <NPCName>Semeru</> would loosen up a bit, so I could chill more.//<portrait=surprised>Oops, hope he didn't hear that.

Text.SourceString: Love just hanging around town, sitting back and watching land-dwellers go by.
Text.LocalizedString: Love just hanging around town, sitting back and watching land-dwellers go by.

Text.SourceString: You've got snow on your head.
Text.LocalizedString: You've got snow on your head.

Text.SourceString: I better warm up before I turn into a frozen fish over here!
Text.LocalizedString: I better warm up before I turn into a frozen fish over here!

Text.SourceString: Woke up feeling super fresh today. Must be this crisp, cold weather.
Text.LocalizedString: Woke up feeling super fresh today. Must be this crisp, cold weather.

Text.SourceString: We're scheduled to get influenza vaccinations soon, now that we're around land dwellers and their flus.//Gotta make sure we're protected too.
Text.LocalizedString: We're scheduled to get influenza vaccinations soon, now that we're around land dwellers and their flus.//Gotta make sure we're protected too.

Text.SourceString: I snuck up and put my cold hands on <NPCName>Semeru</>'s neck this morning, ha! His face was priceless.
Text.LocalizedString: I snuck up and put my cold hands on <NPCName>Semeru</>'s neck this morning, ha! His face was priceless.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I miss hanging out with <NPCName>Agung</>. <NPCName>Semeru</>'s no fun to tease.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I miss hanging out with <NPCName>Agung</>. <NPCName>Semeru</>'s no fun to tease.

Text.SourceString: My hands are freezing! Wanna feel?
Text.LocalizedString: My hands are freezing! Wanna feel?

Text.SourceString: I wanna go outside and play in the water. We've got rain here, and it falls right from the sky!
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna go outside and play in the water. We've got rain here, and it falls right from the sky!

Text.SourceString: I wanna go outside and play in the water. We've got rain here, and it falls right from the sky!
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna go outside and play in the water. We've got rain here, and it falls right from the sky!

Text.SourceString: I snuck a taste of the rainwater; it's not the same as our ocean water.//I prefer the ocean's, no offense.
Text.LocalizedString: I snuck a taste of the rainwater; it's not the same as our ocean water.//I prefer the ocean's, no offense.

Text.SourceString: The falling snow is just so pretty. Saw it this morning through my window.
Text.LocalizedString: The falling snow is just so pretty. Saw it this morning through my window.
